{"title":"Canyon releases a limited edition Aeroad designed with Mathieu van der Poel","link":"https://www.cyclingtips.com/2023/05/canyon-aeroad-van-der-poel/","date":1683895380000,"content":"<figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Canyon-Aeroad-CFR-van-der-Poel-bike-riding.jpg?width=1200\" alt=\"Canyon releases a limited edition Aeroad designed with Mathieu van der Poel\" /></figure><p><span>Mathieu van der Poel’s </span><a href=\"https://www.cyclingtips.com/2020/10/2021-canyon-aeroad-coddles-you-with-speed-stiffness-and-comfort/\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Canyon Aeroad</span></a><span> is up for grabs. No, it isn’t his with a custom seatpost clamp bolt up top rather than on the seat tube. Instead, the special-edition bike – dubbed the Canyon Aeroad CFR Disc MVDP – features the same colorway, lining, and build kit as his bike. </span></p>\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Canyon-Aeroad-CFR-van-der-Poel-bike-riding-2.jpg?width=730\" alt=\"Canyon-Aeroad-CFR-van-der-Poel-bike---riding-2\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1280\" srcset=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Canyon-Aeroad-CFR-van-der-Poel-bike-riding-2.jpg?width=650 650w, https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Canyon-Aeroad-CFR-van-der-Poel-bike-riding-2.jpg?width=190 190w\" /><figcaption><span>(Image: Canyon)</span></figcaption></figure>\n<p><strong>Read more:</strong> <a href=\"https://www.cyclingtips.com/2023/05/bike-check-remco-evenepoels-world-champion-specialized-tarmac-sl7/\" target=\"_blank\">Bike check: Remco Evenepoel’s world champion Specialized Tarmac SL7</a></p>\n<p><span>The paint scheme features a racing red colorway used by van der Poel to win both Milan-San Remo and Paris-Roubaix and finish second in the Tour of Flanders. The bike features logoing specific to MVDP. This includes his personal logo on the downtube by the bottom bracket, a 3D MVPD logo on the front of the head tube, and one of his favorite mantras, ‘Poetry in Motion.’</span></p>\n<p><span>The bike features about the same build kit MVDP uses on his team bike. This includes a </span><a href=\"https://www.cyclingtips.com/2021/08/shimano-dura-ace-di2-r9200-first-ride-review/\"><span>Shimano Dura-Ace Di2 R9200</span></a><span> groupset with a matching Dura-Ace C60 wheelset. Canyon provides the CP0018 Aerocockpit handlebar stem combo that is fit-adjustable, as well as their SP0046 aero seatpost.</span></p>\n<figure><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Canyon-Aeroad-CFR-van-der-Poel-bike-bike-side.jpg?width=730\" alt=\"Canyon-Aeroad-CFR-van-der-Poel-bike---bike-side\" width=\"1500\" height=\"844\" srcset=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Canyon-Aeroad-CFR-van-der-Poel-bike-bike-side.jpg?width=650 650w, https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Canyon-Aeroad-CFR-van-der-Poel-bike-bike-side.jpg?width=190 190w\" /><figcaption><span>Nearly the same bike that MVDP rides, just with a tire swap and possibly a slight frame change. (Image: Canyon)</span></figcaption></figure>\n<p><span>The one thing that’s different? This one seems to receive Schwalbe’s Pro One road tires rather than the new </span><a href=\"https://www.cyclingtips.com/2023/05/vittoria-corsa-pro-tire-review/\"><span>Vittoria Corsa Pro tires</span></a><span> that Alpecin-Deceuninck typically uses.</span></p>\n<p><span>Finally, the bike receives van der Poel’s signature Selle Italia Flite Carbino Superflow MVDP saddle.</span></p>\n<p><span>As one would expect, the bike is a limited run. See more about it at </span><a href=\"https://www.canyon.com/en-gb/road-bikes/aero-bikes/aeroad/\"><span>canyon.com</span></a><span>.</span></p>\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Canyon-Aeroad-CFR-van-der-Poel-bike-seattube.jpg?width=730\" alt=\"Canyon-Aeroad-CFR-van-der-Poel-bike---seattube\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1500\" srcset=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Canyon-Aeroad-CFR-van-der-Poel-bike-seattube.jpg?width=650 650w, https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Canyon-Aeroad-CFR-van-der-Poel-bike-seattube.jpg?width=190 190w\" /><figcaption><span>(Image: Canyon)</span></figcaption><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Canyon-Aeroad-CFR-van-der-Poel-bike-poetry-in-motion.jpg?width=730\" alt=\"Canyon-Aeroad-CFR-van-der-Poel-bike---poetry-in-motion\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1500\" srcset=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Canyon-Aeroad-CFR-van-der-Poel-bike-poetry-in-motion.jpg?width=650 650w, https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Canyon-Aeroad-CFR-van-der-Poel-bike-poetry-in-motion.jpg?width=190 190w\" /><figcaption>‘Poetry in Motion’ with the MVDP logo right by the bottom bracket. (Image: Canyon)</figcaption></figure></figure>\n<figure>\n<p></p><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Canyon-Aeroad-CFR-van-der-Poel-bike-handlebar.jpg?width=730\" alt=\"Canyon-Aeroad-CFR-van-der-Poel-bike---handlebar\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1500\" srcset=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Canyon-Aeroad-CFR-van-der-Poel-bike-handlebar.jpg?width=650 650w, https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Canyon-Aeroad-CFR-van-der-Poel-bike-handlebar.jpg?width=190 190w\" /><figcaption>The MVDP special edition features a CP0018 Aerocockpit. (Image: Canyon)</figcaption></figure><figcaption></figcaption><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Canyon-Aeroad-CFR-van-der-Poel-bike-downtube.jpg?width=730\" alt=\"Canyon-Aeroad-CFR-van-der-Poel-bike---downtube\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1500\" srcset=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Canyon-Aeroad-CFR-van-der-Poel-bike-downtube.jpg?width=650 650w, https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Canyon-Aeroad-CFR-van-der-Poel-bike-downtube.jpg?width=190 190w\" /><figcaption>(Image: Canyon)</figcaption></figure></figure>","author":"Alvin Holbrook","siteTitle":"CyclingTips","siteHash":"30feca30fb3902119bf2da6559e7337232527b61c9abe0a00f5d7543c6aa6c84","entryHash":"4b72f5d451427eb41bd62239fa51371b59f89baf309a071ae93737ac06edda17","category":"Cycling"}